This paper discusses provenance for transactional updates, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also introduces an extension to the semiring provenance model and proposes a declarative form of replay, which are topics that fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses concurrency control protocols, which is a topic that falls under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses implementation and efficiency, which are topics that fall under software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
